# Critical Audit Report: Service and Repository Files Comparison

## 1. airlineMiles.service.ts

**Source (card-place):**
```typescript
import { airlineMilesApi } from '../api';
import type { AirlineMilesTokenParams, AirlineMilesTokenResponse } from '../models';

export class AirlineMilesService {
  async getToken(params: AirlineMilesTokenParams): Promise<AirlineMilesTokenResponse> {
    return airlineMilesApi.getToken(params);
  }
}

export const airlineMilesService = new AirlineMilesService();
```

**Target (rewardprogram):**
```typescript
import { AirlineMilesRepository } from '../repository/airlineMiles.repository';
import type { AirlineMilesTokenParams, AirlineMilesTokenResponse } from '../models';

export class AirlineMilesService {
  private readonly repository: AirlineMilesRepository;

  constructor() {
    this.repository = new AirlineMilesRepository();
  }

  async getToken(params: AirlineMilesTokenParams): Promise<AirlineMilesTokenResponse> {
    return this.repository.getToken(params);
  }
}

export const airlineMilesService = new AirlineMilesService();
```

- **Logic changes:** ARCHITECTURAL CHANGE - Target introduces a repository layer abstraction. Source calls API directly; target delegates to repository.
- **Import path changes:** 
  - Source: `'../api'` (direct API import)
  - Target: `'../repository/airlineMiles.repository'` (repository import)
- **Status:** ⚠️ ARCHITECTURAL CHANGE (functionally equivalent if repository delegates to API)

---

## 2. parameter.service.ts

**Source (card-place):** 31 lines
**Target (rewardprogram):** 31 lines

- **Logic changes:** NONE - Byte-for-byte identical
- **Import path changes:** NONE - All imports identical (`../api`, `../repository`, `~/store`, `../models`)
- **Status:** ✅ MATCH

---

## 3. permission.service.ts (card-place) vs invoicesCashbackPermission.service.ts (rewardprogram)

**Source (card-place):**
```typescript
import { getPermissionApi, savePermissionApi } from '../api';
import { mapPermissionResponse } from '../repository';
import { useRootStore } from '~/store';
import { PermissionStatus, type PermissionDocumentInput } from '../models';

export async function checkHasRedeemed(accountId: string): Promise<boolean> {
  const { rewardPermissionActions } = useRootStore.getState();
  try {
    rewardPermissionActions.setStatus(PermissionStatus.LOADING);
    const response = await getPermissionApi({ accountNumber: accountId });
    if (response.status >= 200 && response.status < 300 && response?.data) {
      const permissionValue = mapPermissionResponse(response.data);
      const redeemedAt = permissionValue?.invoiceCashbackRedemption?.redeemedAtDate;
      const hasRedeemed = Boolean(redeemedAt);
      rewardPermissionActions.setHasRedeemed(hasRedeemed);
      return hasRedeemed;
    }
    rewardPermissionActions.setStatus(PermissionStatus.ERROR);
    return false;
  } catch {
    rewardPermissionActions.setStatus(PermissionStatus.ERROR);
    return false;
  }
}

export async function markAsRedeemed(accountId: string): Promise<boolean> {
  const { rewardPermissionActions } = useRootStore.getState();
  try {
    // ... creates document, calls savePermissionApi
    rewardPermissionActions.setHasRedeemed(true);
    return true;
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}
```

